Hello.<br />Recently I've found in <a href="http://dabliogames.blogspot.com.br/2013/05/cartmod-megadrive-1.html" class="postlink">this page</a> a schematic of a MegaDrive game wich uses an 8bit ROM and a circuit to &quot;convert&quot; it to 16 bit. <br />Here's the schematic:<br />conversão 8bits para 16 bits.jpg<br />My doubt is: would this simply work out of the box or the pirate game was somehow altered to make this possible?<br />I know that would be simple to just use 2 8bit ROMs with the odd/even bytes, but this circuit seems interesting, specially to me who only have a single 8bit ROM to try.<br /><br />Thanks in advance.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=7094">Fisher</a> — Thu May 03, 2018 7:25 am</p><hr />
